Python Assignment 01

Topic: Variables and Basic Data Types

Q1. Variable

What is a variable in Python? Write the syntax to create a variable and give one example.

Q2. Rules of Variable Naming

Write any three rules for naming variables in Python. Give one correct and one incorrect example.

Q3. Integer Data Type

What is an integer data type? Write one Python example of an integer variable.

Q4. Float Data Type

What is a float data type? Write one Python example using a decimal value.

Q5. String Data Type

What is a string data type? Write two ways to create a string in Python with examples.

Q6. Boolean Data Type

What is a boolean data type? Write its possible values and one example.

Q7. type() Function

What does the type() function do in Python? Explain with an example.

Q8. input() Function

What is the input() function used for in Python? What is the default data type of input? Give an example.

Q9. Type Casting

What is type casting? Write a Python example to convert a string into an integer.

Q10. Program-Based Question

Write a Python program that takes a number from the user and prints its data type.

Why This Assignment is Good

This assignment covers the fundamental concepts of Python programming such as variables, naming rules, basic data types, user input, and type conversion. It helps beginners build a strong foundation, improve logical thinking, and gain initial hands-on practice, which is essential before moving to more advanced programming topics.
